{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Narrative Theory | cover = | editor = Abby Coykendall, Andrea Kaston Tange | discipline = [[English literature]] | former_names = Journal of Narrative Technique | abbreviation = J. Narrat. Theory | publisher = [[Eastern Michigan University]] | country = United States | frequency = Triennial | history = 1971-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.emich.edu/english/jnt/ | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = http://www.emich.edu/english/jnt/archive.html | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 231790013 | LCCN = sn99047333 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1549-0815 | eISSN = 1548-9248 }} The '''''Journal of Narrative Theory''''' is a triannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[narratology]] in literary fiction.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://narrative.georgetown.edu/wiki/index.php/Journal_of_Narrative_Technique_(journal) |title=Journal of Narrative Technique (journal) |date=20 June 2008 |publisher=The International Society for the Study of Narrative, [[Georgetown University]] |accessdate=20 June 2013}}</ref> The journal was established in 1971 as the ''Journal of Narrative Technique'' and obtained its current title in 1999. It is published by the Department of English at [[Eastern Michigan University]] and the [[editors-in-chief]] are Abby Coykendall and Andrea Kaston Tange. In ''An Introduction to Narratology'', [[Monika Fludernik]] lists it as one of "the most important journals in the field".<ref>{{cite book |last=Fludernik |first=Monika |title=An Introduction to Narratology |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uwmIgqX9WCYC&pg=PA12 |accessdate=20 June 2013 |year=2009 |publisher=[[Taylor & Francis]] |isbn=9780203882887 |page=12}}</ref>
